1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with estimating ego-motion from video streams, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as ego-motion estimation is an important problem in robotics, especially for autonomous navigation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel self-supervised learning model for ego-motion estimation. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing an intelligent system that can estimate ego-motion accurately. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper presents state-of-the-art results on several benchmark datasets, which is a common theme in CVPR papers.
